  "title": "LOGISTICS MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Job Description:</p>\n<p>- Manage, support, plan and organise day-to-day inventory and all inventory control process within the warehouse to ensure smooth operations.</p>\n<p>- Ensure daily warehouse activities are performed in a timely, efficient and accurate manner.</p>\n<p>- Ensure proper and accurate placement of all goods</p>\n<p>- Support order fulfilment, picking, packing &amp; ensuring on time delivery of merchandise and minimal error in fulfilment orders</p>\n<p>- Provide leadership and guidance to the warehouse team (about 10 pax), including training, scheduling, and performance management</p>\n<p>- Work closely with retail operations and cross functional teams to resolve daily operational issues.</p>\n<p>- Continuously evaluate warehouse processes and identify opportunities for improvement to enhance efficiency and productivity.</p>\n<p>- Establish and maintain Standard Operation Procedures (SOP).</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Job Requirements:</p>\n<p>- At least a Diploma in Logistic, Supply Chain Management or any related field.</p>\n<p>- Possess at least 3 years of managerial experience in Retail Logistic, or Supply Chain.</p>\n<p>- Proficient in Microsoft Office, ERP/WMS experience is an added advantage</p>\n<p>- Able to handle up to 20kg of load</p>\n<p>- Demonstrated leadership abilities with a track record of effectively managing teams and fostering a positive work environment.</p>\n<p>- Candidates with less than 3 years of managerial experience may be considered for a supervisor position</p>\n<p><br></p>",
